<exercise number="35"><statement><p>Colonial Airline has a commuter flight between Richmond and Washington, a distance of 100 miles. The plane flies at <m>x</m> miles per hour in still air. Today there is a steady wind from the north at 10 miles per hour.<ol lanel="a">
	<li>How long will the flight from Richmond to Washington take?</li>
	<li>How long will the flight from Washington to Richmond take?</li>
	<li>How long will a round trip take?</li>
	<li>Evaluate your fractions in parts (a)-(c) for <m>x=150</m>.</li></ol></p></statement>
<answer><p><ol label="a">
	<li><p><m>\dfrac{100}{x-10} </m> hrs</p></li>
	<li><p><m>\dfrac{100}{x+10} </m> hrs</p></li>
	<li><p><m>\dfrac{200x}{x^2-100} </m> hrs</p></li>
	<li><p><m>\dfrac{5}{7} </m> hrs, <m>\dfrac{5}{8} </m> hrs, <m>\dfrac{75}{56} </m> hrs, </p></li>
</ol></p></answer></exercise>

